        "# IDX Market Primer\n",
        "\n",
        "**Objective:** Establish foundational understanding of Indonesia Stock Exchange (IDX) mechanics, key sectors, and macro drivers.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Key Components:\n",
        "- Trading hours and settlement periods\n",
        "- Sector weights and liquidity focus (LQ45 vs IDX30)\n",
        "- Macro drivers affecting the market\n",
        "- Data availability and sources\n",
        "- Regulatory environment\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 1. IDX Market Mechanics\n",
        "\n",
        "**Trading Hours:**\n",
        "- Monday to Thursday: 09:00 - 12:00 WIB and 13:30 - 15:49 WIB\n",
        "- Friday: Shortened hours (09:00 - 12:00 WIB)\n",
        "\n",
        "**Settlement:** T+2 (two business days after trade)\n",
        "\n",
        "**Lot Size:** 100 shares per lot\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Example data fetching with yfinance\n",
        "try:\n",
        "    # Test the basic connection to IDX data\n",
        "    ticker = 'BBCA.JK'  # Bank Central Asia (one of LQ45)\n",
        "    data = yf.download(ticker, start='2023-01-01', end='2023-12-31')\n",
        "    print(f\"Data fetched successfully for {ticker}\")\n",
        "    print(\"\\nSample Data:\")\n",
        "    print(data.head())\n",
        "except Exception as e:\n",
        "    print(f\"Error fetching data: {e}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 2. Key Sectors and Weightings\n",
        "\n",
        "**Major Sector Weights (Approximate):**\n",
        "- Financials ~40% weight in JKSE\n",
        "- Commodities (Coal, Palm Oil, Nickel)\n",
        - Consumer Goods\n",
        "- Industrials\n",
        "- Utilities\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Example: Fetch data for multiple LQ45 stocks to understand sector spread\n",
        "lq45_stocks = ['BBCA.JK', 'TLKM.JK', 'ASII.JK', 'UNVR.JK']\n",
        "\n",
        "# Initialize empty dictionary to store data\n",
        "stock_data = {}\n",
        "\n",
        "for stock in lq45_stocks:\n",
        "    try:\n",
        "        data = yf.download(stock, start='2023-01-01', end='2023-12-31')\n",
        "        stock_data[stock] = data\n",
        "        print(f\"Successfully fetched {stock} with shape: {data.shape}\")\n",
        "    except Exception as e:\n",
        "        print(f\"Error fetching {stock}: {e}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 3. Macro Drivers\n",
        "\n",
        "**Key Economic Indicators:**\n",
        "- Bank Indonesia (BI) 7-day repo rate\n",
        "- IDR/USD exchange rate\n",
        "- Global commodity prices (Nickel, Palm Oil)\n",
        "- ASEAN/China macroeconomic spillovers\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 4. Volatility Analysis - GARCH Model\n",
        "\n",
        "Using the GARCH model to analyze volatility regimes in IDX data.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Sample GARCH volatility analysis\n",
        "# We'll use a simple implementation\n",
        "\n",
        "def garch_volatility_analysis(data):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Simple GARCH-like volatility calculation\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    # Calculate daily returns\n",
        "    returns = data['Close'].pct_change().dropna()\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Calculate rolling volatility (20-day)\n",
        "    vol_rolling = returns.rolling(window=20).std() * np.sqrt(252)  # Annualized\n",
        "    \n",
        "    return vol_rolling"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 5. Correlation Analysis Matrix\n",
        "\n",
        "Analyzing correlation between key sectors and market performance.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Sample correlation analysis\n",
        "def calculate_sector_correlations(data_dict):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Calculate correlations between different sectors (stocks)\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    # Extract returns from each stock's data\n",
        "    returns_dict = {}\n",
        "\n",
        "    for ticker, df in data_dict.items():\n",
        "        if not df.empty:\n",
        "            returns = df['Close'].pct_change().dropna()\n",
        "            returns_dict[ticker] = returns\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Create DataFrame with all returns\n",
        "    try:\n",
        "        returns_df = pd.DataFrame(returns_dict)\n",
        "        correlation_matrix = returns_df.corr()\n",
        "        \n",
        "        print(\"Correlation Matrix (Sample):\")\n",
        "        print(correlation_matrix)\n",
        "\n",
        "        return correlation_matrix\n",
        "    except Exception as e:\n",
        "        print(f\"Error in correlation analysis: {e}\")\n",
        "        return None"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 6. Data Quality Assessment\n",
        "\n",
        "**Emerging Market Considerations:**\n",
        "- Holidays affecting data availability\n",
        "- Thin order books during certain hours\n",
        - Forward-fill implementation for missing data gaps"
      ]
    },
    {
      "code",
